<BaseLayout title="Evidence Policy" description="PipFury separates confirmed evidence from thesis, assumption, invalidation, and lesson."><section class="section"><div class="container terminal-card p-8 md:p-10"><span class="pill">Evidence Policy</span><h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-5xl font-bold">Every claim should show its work.</h1><div class="prose mt-8"><p>PipFury separates confirmed evidence from working thesis. A chart read is not treated as truth simply because it sounds convincing. Each serious analysis should show chart context, evidence observed, invalidation, outcome status, and lesson after review.</p><h2>Evidence labels</h2><ul><li><strong>Confirmed evidence:</strong> what price or volume has already shown.</li><li><strong>Working thesis:</strong> a possible interpretation, not certainty.</li><li><strong>Assumption:</strong> something not yet confirmed.</li><li><strong>Invalidation:</strong> what proves the idea wrong.</li><li><strong>Lesson:</strong> what the trader should learn.</li></ul></div></div></section></BaseLayout>